Data Types:
Java Script is dynamic language so there is no need to mention data type before declaring variables.
Two types:
1)	Primitive Data type: Predefined and stores only single values.
•	Number: Integer, Floats.
•	String: Stream of characters enclosed in quotes.
-single, double, backtick.
Backtick is introduced ES6 version.
•	Boolean : true , false.
•	Null: empty value or no value.
•	Undefined:  declared variable with no value
2)	Non-Primitive Data type: Objects ,Arrays.
To check the datatype we us – typeOf operator.

Condition: An expression that evaluates the result(true or false)
Console.log(5>4)
Conditional Statements:
To execute a block of code only when the condition is true.


Practical implementation:
